1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:01,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,799
<i>[A Bird That Doesn't Sing]</i>

3
00:00:10,799 --> 00:00:12,740
<i>Episode 7</i>

4
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,978
Lift your face.

5
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,716
What's wrong?

6
00:00:33,716 --> 00:00:35,049
She said something to you?

7
00:00:35,049 --> 00:00:37,150
Was she giving you a hard time?

8
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:39,495
It's not that.

9
00:00:42,260 --> 00:00:43,700
No.

10
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,263
No.

11
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:48,090
No, Mom.

12
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:50,569
No, Mom.

13
00:00:50,569 --> 00:00:52,311
Don't come near me.

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,510
Was that her mom?

15
00:01:04,510 --> 00:01:06,013
What?

16
00:01:06,013 --> 00:01:07,715
Oh, nothing.

17
00:01:08,105 --> 00:01:09,227
Here.

18
00:01:22,311 --> 00:01:26,188
<i>For twelve years,
I lived getting beat up.</i>

19
00:01:26,188 --> 00:01:27,745
<i>You think I would be scared of this?</i>

20
00:01:27,745 --> 00:01:29,602
<i>Dying?</i>

21
00:01:29,602 --> 00:01:31,117
<i>I'm not scared at all.</i>

22
00:01:31,117 --> 00:01:35,810
I don't care if you harass me,
just don't harass my daughter!

23
00:01:35,810 --> 00:01:40,377
Oh Yu Mi, I never abandoned you.

24
00:01:41,169 --> 00:01:45,075
Seven years ago, you were
the one who left me.

25
00:01:49,138 --> 00:01:52,573
From now on, I'll protect you.

26
00:01:54,099 --> 00:01:59,466
I'll never let go
of these hands ever again.

27
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,449
My daughter...

28
00:02:08,263 --> 00:02:10,990
I'll protect you.

29
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,139
<i>Ms. Oh, please go to the VIP room.</i>

30
00:02:32,304 --> 00:02:35,887
Please go to the Soo Yeon Cosmetics
headquarters in Sinsa Dong.

31
00:02:41,868 --> 00:02:44,372
A little more on the inner lips.

32
00:02:55,116 --> 00:02:57,474
I love it.
Nice, right?

33
00:02:59,099 --> 00:03:01,572
I see why you were
so adamant about this.

34
00:03:01,572 --> 00:03:03,675
It's a great idea.

35
00:03:04,431 --> 00:03:08,609
I told you, my Ha Nui did it again.

36
00:03:08,609 --> 00:03:10,627
"My Ha Nui"?

37
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,479
Okay.

38
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:15,026
- Ms. Oh, are you finished?
- Yes.

39
00:03:15,026 --> 00:03:16,467
Everyone is going
to talk about how pretty

40
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:17,906
the female employees at
Soo Yeon Cosmetics are.

41
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:19,979
Everybody looks so good.

42
00:03:20,683 --> 00:03:23,717
How about if you include
average people as models?

43
00:03:23,717 --> 00:03:25,457
They can be of all different ages.

44
00:03:25,729 --> 00:03:26,846
That's a good idea.

45
00:03:27,366 --> 00:03:29,878
I think that would be nice.

46
00:03:29,878 --> 00:03:32,074
This one will be a big hit too.

47
00:03:32,074 --> 00:03:34,117
You know she doesn't
just complement anyone.

48
00:03:34,117 --> 00:03:35,437
Oh, yeah.

49
00:03:35,437 --> 00:03:39,211
<i>Way to go, we rock, yay, yay...</i>

50
00:03:39,211 --> 00:03:43,400
On that note, I'll treat
everyone to lunch today!

51
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,412
Let's go.

52
00:03:44,412 --> 00:03:48,451
Of course, you don't say
you'll treat me to lunch.

53
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,706
- Come with us, Director.
- No thanks.

54
00:03:52,706 --> 00:03:54,214
I have lunch plans.

55
00:03:55,084 --> 00:03:57,829
Sexy Q came out nice.

56
00:03:57,829 --> 00:03:59,526
And you've got a good
marketing concept.

57
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,358
Your mom must be so proud.

58
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:06,920
I wish I had a daughter like you.

59
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:16,733
Hold on.

60
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,000
Yu Mi!

61
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,783
Let's go eat lunch together.
You didn't even eat breakfast.

62
00:04:23,783 --> 00:04:25,415
I'm not that hungry.

63
00:04:25,415 --> 00:04:27,122
You go eat.

64
00:04:27,122 --> 00:04:28,629
Yu Mi!

65
00:04:33,185 --> 00:04:39,620
You haven't been smiling, sleeping,
or eating well for these past few days.

66
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:44,047
If I were you, and you were me,
what would you say?

67
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:49,728
I'm so disappointed in myself that
I can't be of any help to you.

68
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:53,437
Give me a hint.

69
00:04:53,437 --> 00:04:55,322
How can I help you?

70
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:59,800
I just don't have much appetite.

71
00:05:00,677 --> 00:05:04,725
Did you hear from your mother?

72
00:05:08,928 --> 00:05:12,529
Why do you ask that so suddenly?

73
00:05:12,529 --> 00:05:18,300
That customer that walked
out of your makeup room...

74
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,769
Is she her?

75
00:05:21,019 --> 00:05:23,166
No...

76
00:05:23,166 --> 00:05:25,538
She's my regular customer.

77
00:05:25,538 --> 00:05:27,822
- What do you want to eat?
- Something expensive.

78
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:32,514
Ha Nui, don't worry about me.
Go eat something good.

79
00:05:32,514 --> 00:05:35,519
I'll eat if I get hungry.
I just don't have much appetite.

80
00:05:35,519 --> 00:05:37,783
You worked hard,
you should come with us.

81
00:05:37,783 --> 00:05:39,994
Let's just say that I ate.

82
00:05:42,312 --> 00:05:44,017
Yu Mi...

83
00:05:45,129 --> 00:05:49,853
What does it feel like
to have no appetite?

84
00:05:49,853 --> 00:05:52,285
How is it possible
to have no appetite?

85
00:05:52,963 --> 00:05:56,050
It drives me nuts that
I have so much appetite.

86
00:06:01,387 --> 00:06:03,870
- What diet?
- You can eat.

87
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:06,266
- No, I need to diet.
- What are you talking about?

88
00:06:07,281 --> 00:06:10,992
I feel like there's a wall.
It's so upsetting.

89
00:06:11,939 --> 00:06:14,603
But I'm still so worried about her.

90
00:06:14,603 --> 00:06:18,367
"Let's not care.
She probably wants to be alone."

91
00:06:18,367 --> 00:06:20,242
"Let's wait until
she feels like talking."

92
00:06:20,242 --> 00:06:21,411
I know all this

93
00:06:21,411 --> 00:06:24,927
- but I still get worried.
- That's who you are.

94
00:06:26,608 --> 00:06:29,906
Does she have something
that she can't share with me?

95
00:06:31,067 --> 00:06:33,062
She didn't say anything
to your mother, right?

96
00:06:34,824 --> 00:06:39,218
She isn't eating at all.
I'm afraid she'll faint.

97
00:06:40,788 --> 00:06:44,490
Do you have any idea
how I can help her?

98
00:06:52,935 --> 00:06:54,338
What is it?

99
00:06:58,735 --> 00:07:00,653
What is it now?

100
00:07:05,423 --> 00:07:10,000
Healing food for the one you love?

101
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,625
Healing food.

102
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:22,622
I'll be right there.

103
00:07:22,622 --> 00:07:24,067
I just need a few minutes.

104
00:07:25,672 --> 00:07:27,319
Where are you going?

105
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:29,725
- Going out for lunch?
- Yes.

106
00:07:30,471 --> 00:07:32,555
I'll be back.

107
00:07:35,091 --> 00:07:38,954
- Shes a bit strange these days, no?
- She must be worried about something.

108
00:07:38,954 --> 00:07:43,663
- But she's not the type to talk.
- I feel bad for her mother-in-law.

109
00:07:43,663 --> 00:07:47,596
She's a talented girl,
but she has a bad personality.

110
00:07:47,596 --> 00:07:50,170
Ha Nui's the one with
great personality.

111
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:53,505
She's got a lot of heartache,
but she can't show it.

112
00:07:53,505 --> 00:07:55,803
She has no choice
but to keep it all in.

113
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:59,822
Yu Mi reminds me of the old you.

114
00:07:59,822 --> 00:08:02,201
I don't like gloomy people.
They're so frustrating.

115
00:08:20,450 --> 00:08:22,965
Don't even think about hiding
me in a corner somewhere.

116
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,886
- Sit down.
- There are so many people here.

117
00:08:25,886 --> 00:08:28,274
- Come on, let's get out.
- When you were twenty-two

118
00:08:28,274 --> 00:08:30,855
and you tried to kill yourself on
that bridge after getting dumped

119
00:08:30,855 --> 00:08:33,250
there were people there
when I dragged you down.

120
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,472
When you blew all your
money on horse racing

121
00:08:35,472 --> 00:08:38,094
and I brought you home when
you were sleeping on the streets

122
00:08:38,094 --> 00:08:41,120
I didn't try to hide you.

123
00:08:41,701 --> 00:08:43,730
Why are you bringing that up now?

124
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:47,043
Jo Dal Yeon might come to see you.

125
00:08:47,671 --> 00:08:49,336
Why?

126
00:08:49,336 --> 00:08:51,037
Did something happen?

127
00:08:51,037 --> 00:08:53,046
I just met with her.

128
00:08:53,046 --> 00:08:54,932
- We fought a little.
- What?

129
00:08:57,056 --> 00:08:59,596
Why would you provoke that crazy woman?

130
00:08:59,596 --> 00:09:02,148
When I think about that night,
I pee in my sleep.

131
00:09:02,148 --> 00:09:04,698
You fought when you should
be crawling before her?

132
00:09:04,698 --> 00:09:06,993
Why would you poke around the beehive?

133
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,379
She harassed Yu Mi.

134
00:09:10,379 --> 00:09:12,006
How can I do nothing?

135
00:09:12,006 --> 00:09:14,505
I put her in her place.

136
00:09:15,408 --> 00:09:17,889
- Where?
- In front of Yu Mi.

137
00:09:18,399 --> 00:09:19,769
What?

138
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:26,601
I apologize in her place.

139
00:09:26,601 --> 00:09:28,731
My mom made a mistake.

140
00:09:28,731 --> 00:09:31,152
How touching.

141
00:09:31,152 --> 00:09:32,953
What's with you two?

142
00:09:32,955 --> 00:09:35,918
- I'm sorry.
- Why are you always so sorry?

143
00:09:35,918 --> 00:09:38,206
I'm so sick and tired of
hearing that from you.

144
00:09:38,206 --> 00:09:40,456
Are you scared that
I'll do something to your mom?

145
00:09:40,456 --> 00:09:45,155
Or have you still not been able
to get rid of your nice girl complex?

146
00:09:47,176 --> 00:09:48,724
I'm sorry.

147
00:09:48,724 --> 00:09:52,250
No matter how much you beg,
I won't forgive your mom.

148
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:56,042
I can't say that I have
nothing to be ashamed of.

149
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:59,001
But at least I never ran away
with someone else's money.

150
00:09:59,035 --> 00:10:03,687
If people like your mom live well,
how is that fair?

151
00:10:03,687 --> 00:10:05,248
Yu Mi.

152
00:10:05,248 --> 00:10:07,691
I'm really curious.

153
00:10:07,691 --> 00:10:12,456
Are you doing this because
you really care about your mom?

154
00:10:15,764 --> 00:10:18,365
My grandmother raised me

155
00:10:19,106 --> 00:10:20,916
after my mother ran away.

156
00:10:20,916 --> 00:10:24,217
After my grandmother passed away,
I went through so much hardship.

157
00:10:24,913 --> 00:10:28,384
If I ever meet my mother again,
I would never forgive her.

158
00:10:29,099 --> 00:10:31,831
What's your true feeling?

159
00:10:34,519 --> 00:10:37,582
Yu Mi must have been so shocked.
She's such a fragile girl.

160
00:10:37,582 --> 00:10:41,907
Is that why she called me "Madame
after not seeing me for seven years?

161
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:45,788
- What do you mean?
- She's my own daughter, I know her well.

162
00:10:46,808 --> 00:10:48,178
She's a strong girl.

163
00:10:48,952 --> 00:10:50,875
I really don't know.

164
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,001
So Yu Mi's okay.

165
00:10:53,001 --> 00:10:56,714
You irked that crazy lady, what
if she treats you even worse?

166
00:10:56,714 --> 00:11:00,100
Get 300 million in Nam Gyu's name
and send it to me quick.

167
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,831
You think 300 million is a joke?

168
00:11:03,942 --> 00:11:05,886
Do you know what kind
of trouble he'll be in

169
00:11:05,886 --> 00:11:07,830
if they find out he spent company money?

170
00:11:07,830 --> 00:11:10,022
After everything he's done
for the company

171
00:11:10,022 --> 00:11:12,635
he can't even touch that money?

172
00:11:37,489 --> 00:11:40,065
What a good life...

173
00:11:40,845 --> 00:11:44,273
Soo Yeon Cosmetics was nothing
but a small start-up company.

174
00:11:44,273 --> 00:11:46,596
Who do they think made
the company grow this much?

175
00:11:46,596 --> 00:11:49,433
Using a few hundred million won
is embezzlement?

176
00:11:54,522 --> 00:11:56,269
Get me the money by today.

177
00:11:57,032 --> 00:12:00,404
Nam Gyu's working hard trying
to expand into the Chinese market.

178
00:12:00,404 --> 00:12:04,168
I should be helping him, not thinking
about ways to steal company money!

179
00:12:04,168 --> 00:12:06,739
My conscience won't allow me.

180
00:12:08,932 --> 00:12:10,303
Oh my God...

181
00:12:10,303 --> 00:12:12,365
No way.

182
00:12:14,745 --> 00:12:16,919
You should go in, first.
I'll be right there.

183
00:12:16,919 --> 00:12:18,722
Let's go.

184
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:22,860
Hello.

185
00:12:23,971 --> 00:12:26,427
What are you doing here?

186
00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:31,089
I was just passing by, and I saw a cafe.
You work here?

187
00:12:31,089 --> 00:12:33,835
Yes, I wasn't sure if
it was really you.

188
00:12:33,835 --> 00:12:35,782
You look so elegant.

189
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:39,275
Have a cup of coffee, my treat.

190
00:12:39,275 --> 00:12:40,885
No.

191
00:12:41,544 --> 00:12:43,485
It's good to see you here.

192
00:12:43,485 --> 00:12:45,884
And I want to thank you
for putting ointment on Min Ji.

193
00:12:49,817 --> 00:12:51,203
What the heck?

194
00:12:51,203 --> 00:12:52,854
Why are they so close?

195
00:12:52,854 --> 00:12:54,600
They are smiling.

196
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,693
They know each other?

197
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:59,006
What the heck is going on?

198
00:13:05,976 --> 00:13:10,291
Seeing you out like this,
you seem so different.

199
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:11,860
You are so glamorous.

200
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:14,320
I'll take it as a compliment.

201
00:13:21,154 --> 00:13:25,674
Our department just
launched a new lipstick.

202
00:13:25,674 --> 00:13:29,475
Maybe that's why, but I've
been noticing everyone's lips.

203
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:31,975
It must be a job-related illness.

204
00:13:31,975 --> 00:13:34,480
I don't think so.

205
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,573
What?

206
00:13:35,573 --> 00:13:38,596
An artist getting cervical disc
or intervertebral disc...

207
00:13:38,596 --> 00:13:42,571
Someone who gets varicose veins
from working while standing all day...

208
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:44,754
Those are what you call
job-related illnesses.

209
00:13:44,754 --> 00:13:49,631
People who do hard labor
will laugh at you.

210
00:13:49,631 --> 00:13:51,703
Yeah?

211
00:13:52,413 --> 00:13:54,692
I guess so.

212
00:13:55,495 --> 00:13:56,865
Oh.

213
00:13:57,679 --> 00:14:01,019
I work for the product development team.

214
00:14:01,019 --> 00:14:08,533
We want to use employees and other
regular people to model our new lipstick.

215
00:14:08,533 --> 00:14:11,706
I would like you to be part of it.

216
00:14:11,706 --> 00:14:13,597
As a model?

217
00:14:15,150 --> 00:14:16,726
I'm taken aback.

218
00:14:16,726 --> 00:14:18,408
And a little flattered.

219
00:14:18,408 --> 00:14:20,620
When do I have to let you know by?

220
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:22,283
Tonight?

221
00:14:22,283 --> 00:14:25,173
I have a cooking class
in the afternoon.

222
00:14:25,173 --> 00:14:27,236
You can call me tomorrow morning.

223
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,371
You take cooking lessons?

224
00:14:29,371 --> 00:14:30,759
Getting ready for marriage?

225
00:14:30,759 --> 00:14:33,866
I don't know what happened to my sister.

226
00:14:33,866 --> 00:14:36,912
She can't sleep or eat well these days

227
00:14:36,912 --> 00:14:38,869
so I want to make her yummy food.

228
00:14:38,869 --> 00:14:43,804
And my dad's birthday is coming up,
so I want to cook for him myself.

229
00:14:44,452 --> 00:14:47,195
You are very considerate,
unlike young people these days.

230
00:14:47,195 --> 00:14:49,996
I'll think about it, and call you.

231
00:14:49,996 --> 00:14:51,982
Okay, I'll be waiting.

232
00:14:51,982 --> 00:14:53,500
Then.

233
00:14:59,225 --> 00:15:02,421
You want to cook for
your father's birthday?

234
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:08,876
Too bad, by then, he'll
be over at our house.

235
00:15:09,859 --> 00:15:11,581
Keep dreaming.

236
00:15:12,581 --> 00:15:16,571
He should have received
the gift by now.

237
00:15:16,571 --> 00:15:19,000
Just like the green forest

238
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:25,543
that grows despite
the heavy rainstorms and strong sunrays

239
00:15:25,543 --> 00:15:27,409
using nature's wisdom

240
00:15:27,409 --> 00:15:31,067
Soo Yeon Cosmetics will bring you
clean and clear complexion.

241
00:15:31,738 --> 00:15:33,764
We will bring you...

242
00:15:35,971 --> 00:15:37,206
Who is there?

243
00:15:37,206 --> 00:15:38,660
Mr. Oh?

244
00:15:39,245 --> 00:15:41,446
This package arrived from Korea.

245
00:15:41,446 --> 00:15:42,990
From Korea?

246
00:15:42,990 --> 00:15:44,017
Yes.

247
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,184
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

248
00:15:52,701 --> 00:15:53,904
Yu Mi.

249
00:15:53,904 --> 00:15:56,946
Wow, I wonder what she sent.

250
00:16:10,812 --> 00:16:13,903
"Package was delivered"?

251
00:16:16,027 --> 00:16:17,407
What's this?

252
00:16:21,008 --> 00:16:22,629
Mom!

253
00:16:25,201 --> 00:16:26,259
Mom!

254
00:16:29,304 --> 00:16:31,268
Your mom's not here, yet.

255
00:16:31,268 --> 00:16:32,735
Should I call her?

256
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:43,125
- What?
- Your daughter came by.

257
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:45,367
She came to apologize for you.

258
00:16:45,367 --> 00:16:47,333
<i>She works in your place.</i>

259
